What:		/sys/kernel/vas_segs
Date:		Mar 2017
Contact:	Till Smejkal <till.smejkal@gmail.com>
Description:
		Kernel interface for VAS segments.

		The /sys/kernel/vas_seg directory contains subdirectories for each
		VAS segment that is currently known to the kernel.

What:		/sys/kernel/vas_segs/<seg>
Date:		Mar 2017
Contact:	Till Smejkal <till.smejkal@gmail.com>
Description:
		The directories for each VAS segment contain various files that can be
        used to collect additional information about it.

What:		/sys/kernel/vas_segs/<seg>/name
Date:		Mar 2017
Contact:	Till Smejkal <till.smejkal@gmail.com>
Description:
		A read-only attribute that can be used to get the user-defined
		name of the corresponding VAS segment.

What:		/sys/kernel/vas_segs/<seg>/mode
Date:		Mar 2017
Contact:	Till Smejkal <till.smejkal@gmail.com>
Description:
		A read-only attribute that can be used to get the access
		permissions of the corresponding VAS segment.

What:		/sys/kernel/vas_segs/<seg>/user
Date:		Mar 2017
Contact:	Till Smejkal <till.smejkal@gmail.com>
Description:
		A read-only attribute that can be used to get the owning user of
		the corresponding VAS segment.

What:		/sys/kernel/vas_segs/<seg>/group
Date:		Mar 2017
Contact:	Till Smejkal <till.smejkal@gmail.com>
Description:
		A read-only attribute that can be used to get the owning group
		of the corresponding VAS segment.

What:		/sys/kernel/vas_segs/<seg>/region
Date:		Mar 2017
Contact:	Till Smejkal <till.smejkal@gmail.com>
Description:
        A read-only attribute that can be used to get the virtual memory region
        that is covered by the corresponding VAS segment.

